video.title: House of Cards
video.synopsis: With Frank out of the picture, Claire Underwood steps fully into her own as the first woman president, but faces formidable threats to her legacy.

episodes.synopsis: When the newly elected President reneges on a promise, Frank and Claire decide to sever all allegiances and toss the rules out the window.
episodes.title: Chapter 1

episodes.synopsis: Frank uses a young reporter, Zoe Barnes, to spin a story that puts the White House on its heels. Claire makes a cold-blooded move at work.
episodes.title: Chapter 2

episodes.synopsis: Frank must leave union negotiations to deal with a crisis in his home district. Zoe negotiates the politics of being a journalist on the rise.
episodes.title: Chapter 3

episodes.synopsis: Frank shakes down the Congressional leadership. Peter Russo must choose between politics and family.
episodes.title: Chapter 4

episodes.synopsis: Frank's fight over the Education Bill threatens Claire's own ambitions. Zoe mixes work and play.
episodes.title: Chapter 5

episodes.synopsis: Frank strikes back at the striking teachers. Claire is caught off guard by a deathbed confession.
episodes.title: Chapter 6

episodes.synopsis: Frank wins a major battle, but doesn't pause to rest on his laurels. Peter must face his past. Stamper hushes a secret.
episodes.title: Chapter 7

episodes.synopsis: Frank is honored at his alma mater, while Peter returns to Philly. Both men tackle unfinished business.
episodes.title: Chapter 8

episodes.synopsis: Russo hits the road with V.P. Matthews. Frank and Stamper try to whip up support in Congress. Claire looks out for herself.
episodes.title: Chapter 9

episodes.synopsis: Rebellion on all fronts. Claire defies Frank, Zoe finds comfort in someone new, and Peter makes an ultimatum.
episodes.title: Chapter 10

episodes.synopsis: Claire fuels an old flame. Peter wrestles with his demons. Frank crosses the point of no return.
episodes.title: Chapter 11

episodes.synopsis: Frank must make an unforeseen detour. Zoe, Lucas and Janine get closer to the truth.
episodes.title: Chapter 12

episodes.synopsis: Frank scrambles to keep his plan on track. Claire is haunted by choices old and new. Zoe poses a serious threat.
episodes.title: Chapter 13

episodes.synopsis: The Underwoods tackle two threats that could bring their plans to ruin. Frank grooms his replacement as Whip. Claire goes on the offensive.
episodes.title: Chapter 14

episodes.synopsis: Frank puts China in the cross-hairs. Claire confronts a painful trauma from her past. Lucas Goodwin presses for the truth.
episodes.title: Chapter 15

episodes.synopsis: Tension rises between Frank and Raymond Tusk as the situation with China deteriorates. A battle in the Senate pits Frank against the Republicans.
episodes.title: Chapter 16

episodes.synopsis: A terror scare at the Capitol traps Frank with a resentful Donald Blythe. Claire gives a live interview that rocks the media.
episodes.title: Chapter 17

episodes.synopsis: Frank back-channels with a Chinese billionaire. Lucas uses extreme measures to expose the Vice President. A shadowy figure joins Team Underwood.
episodes.title: Chapter 18

episodes.synopsis: Amidst an energy crisis, Frank and Tusk end their shaky alliance. Lucas must make a difficult choice. Stamper grows closer to Rachel.
episodes.title: Chapter 19

episodes.synopsis: Despite some friction, the Walkers deepen their friendship with the Underwoods. But it's all-out war between Frank and Tusk.
episodes.title: Chapter 20

episodes.synopsis: The war with Tusk intensifies. Claire influences Tricia Walker politically and domestically. Frank has a show-down with Linda Vasquez.
episodes.title: Chapter 21

episodes.synopsis: Things get personal when Tusk blindsides the Underwoods with a scandal. Freddy and his BBQ joint get caught up in the mix.
episodes.title: Chapter 22

episodes.synopsis: With a military stand-off overseas and potential violence at home, Frank wants to finish off Tusk for good. Claire and Jackie Sharp collide.
episodes.title: Chapter 23

episodes.synopsis: A Special Prosecutor interrogates Frank. Remy Danton tries to keep his options open. Stamper wrestles with his demons.
episodes.title: Chapter 24

episodes.synopsis: Frank finds himself shut out, and Claire makes a difficult sacrifice. Stamper tries to regain control.
episodes.title: Chapter 25

episodes.synopsis: Frank faces annihilation while the nation is in an uproar. Stamper must tie up loose ends. Claire feels the cost of ruthlessness.
episodes.title: Chapter 26

episodes.synopsis: A rocky start for the Underwood Presidency. Frank wants to introduce an ambitious jobs program, while Claire sets her sights on the United Nations.
episodes.title: Chapter 27

episodes.synopsis: Claire’s U.N. bid runs into trouble. Frank fights off mutiny with a bold address to the country.
episodes.title: Chapter 28

episodes.synopsis: The Russian president’s state visit becomes a cold war of wills, and some punks heat things up.
episodes.title: Chapter 29

episodes.synopsis: Claire bypasses Russia at the U.N. Frank tries to outmaneuver a potential challenger and ends up face to face with a higher power.
episodes.title: Chapter 30

episodes.synopsis: Frank declares war on Congress to jump-start his jobs program. Claire spars with the Russian Ambassador.
episodes.title: Chapter 31

episodes.synopsis: Frank and Claire travel to Moscow to negotiate the return of an imprisoned U.S. citizen. Claire takes a stand that jeopardizes their plans.
episodes.title: Chapter 32

episodes.synopsis: The damage is done and the Underwoods must repair it. But deep wounds don't heal fast, and sometimes not at all.
episodes.title: Chapter 33

episodes.synopsis: A hurricane endangers more than just the entire East Coast and Frank must make a difficult choice.
episodes.title: Chapter 34

episodes.synopsis: The Jordan Valley erupts in chaos just as Frank's campaign is picking up steam. Claire gets disturbing intel and counsels him.
episodes.title: Chapter 35

episodes.synopsis: Frank needs to deal with Petrov one on one while Claire tries to preserve the peace-keeping mission. Sacrifices must be made.
episodes.title: Chapter 36

episodes.synopsis: Things turn ugly when Frank, Jackie, and Heather square off during their first debate. Tom joins Claire on the campaign trail.
episodes.title: Chapter 37

episodes.synopsis: Heather Dunbar goes for the jugular, forcing Claire to confront her worst fears. The rift between Frank and Claire widens.
episodes.title: Chapter 38

episodes.synopsis: In the midst of the Iowa caucuses, Frank and Claire must confront hard truths about each other.
episodes.title: Chapter 39

episodes.synopsis: Claire's absence causes problems for Frank on the campaign trail amid rumors of a marital rift. Claire tries to strike out on her own.
episodes.title: Chapter 40

episodes.synopsis: As Claire begins exploring a campaign of her own, she and Frank engage in backdoor political maneuvering. But this time they're not on the same side.
episodes.title: Chapter 41

episodes.synopsis: Claire joins Frank as he stumps in South Carolina, but he doesn't trust her. A disastrous scandal blindsides Frank's campaign on primary day.
episodes.title: Chapter 42

episodes.synopsis: Claire threatens Frank. Frank makes a politically bold move that may provoke Russia. An event at a campaign stop changes everything.
episodes.title: Chapter 43

episodes.synopsis: Claire advises Donald Blythe on dealing with Petrov. Further investigation of Lucas Goodwin dredges up his accusations against Frank.
episodes.title: Chapter 44

episodes.synopsis: Claire clashes with the Secretary of State over her involvement in negotiations with Russia. Dunbar must choose between her campaign and her ethics.
episodes.title: Chapter 45

episodes.synopsis: Frank and Claire adjust to their new reality. The search for Frank's running mate begins. Frank starts a campaign to weaken Conway's strong support.
episodes.title: Chapter 46

episodes.synopsis: Formidable as ever, both Underwoods have their eyes on the big picture as they manipulate a potential running mate and push the gun bill.
episodes.title: Chapter 47

episodes.synopsis: At the convention, Frank and his team publicly push for Catherine Durant to be chosen as his running mate, but privately pursue a different agenda.
episodes.title: Chapter 48

episodes.synopsis: As Frank deals with a new threat to his candidacy, Claire has doubts about their plan. Claire faces a difficult decision concerning her mother.
episodes.title: Chapter 49

episodes.synopsis: Frank ups the ante on the war on terror to counter Conway's public show of strength. Tom joins Claire on the campaign trail.
episodes.title: Chapter 50

episodes.synopsis: Frank asks Will to help deal with extremists threatening to murder hostages. Hammerschmidt digs deeper into the allegations against Frank.
episodes.title: Chapter 51

episodes.synopsis: As the hostage situation continues, Claire secretly negotiates with Yusuf al Ahmadi. Frank confronts Hammerschmidt.
episodes.title: Chapter 52

episodes.synopsis: As Congress debates investigating Frank, he and Claire attempt to stoke fear of terrorism. Tom Yates continues his stay in the White House.
episodes.title: Chapter 53

episodes.synopsis: Frank and his team work to leverage support in key states by any means necessary. Claire learns some upsetting news about one of Frank's friends.
episodes.title: Chapter 54

episodes.synopsis: The day before the election, Conway holds a 24-hour Skype session with voters, while Frank and Claire stump in key states and try to discredit him.
episodes.title: Chapter 55

episodes.synopsis: With a tight race and low voter turnout on Election Day, things look grim for Frank. But he's still got one more trick up his sleeve.
episodes.title: Chapter 56

episodes.synopsis: Nine weeks after Election Day, the Underwoods work to consolidate their power. LeAnn tries to track down a missing Aidan Macallan.
episodes.title: Chapter 57

episodes.synopsis: In the midst of uncertainty, suspected Russian forces take over an American station in Antarctica. Meanwhile, a damaging news leak could hurt Frank.
episodes.title: Chapter 58

episodes.synopsis: When a crisis forces White House personnel to take shelter in a bunker, Commerce Department official Jane Davis negotiates through back channels.
episodes.title: Chapter 59

episodes.synopsis: While Frank attends an elite men's weekend gathering to firm up support, Claire deals with a stranded Russian ship and threats from Petrov.
episodes.title: Chapter 60

episodes.synopsis: Petrov tries to influence affairs in the U.S. Jane discusses her agenda with Claire. With her job at stake, LeAnn reaches out to a reporter for help.
episodes.title: Chapter 61

episodes.synopsis: The Underwoods and their team angle to undermine the revived committee investigating Frank. Hammerschmidt's investigation heats up.
episodes.title: Chapter 62

episodes.synopsis: As the team tries to control fallout from damaging testimony and leaks, everyone is under suspicion and tensions flare between Frank and Claire.
episodes.title: Chapter 63

episodes.synopsis: Frank attempts to stop Cathy from testifying. With Hammerschmidt sniffing out the truth, the Underwoods throw someone close to them under the bus.
episodes.title: Chapter 64

episodes.synopsis: In the wake of a surprising announcement, everything at the White House is shaken up. A decision must be made about whether to go to war.
episodes.title: Chapter 65

episodes.synopsis: As the first woman president, Claire faces increased scrutiny and threats. Sibling power couple Annette and Bill Shepherd attempt to influence policy.
episodes.title: Chapter 66

episodes.synopsis: Claire clashes with the Shepherds and Mark Usher, who pressure her to sign the Future Act. Doug makes an unexpected move.
episodes.title: Chapter 67

episodes.synopsis: The Shepherds push Claire on a Supreme Court nomination. Doug works to find a new path for himself. Claire consults with Jane on Syria.
episodes.title: Chapter 68

episodes.synopsis: As a crisis mounts in Syria, Russian President Viktor Petrov wants to make a deal with Claire. Questions arise about Tom Yates's whereabouts.
episodes.title: Chapter 69

episodes.synopsis: Claire allows her enemies to think she's incapacitated as they plot to remove her from office. Doug's investigation leads him to uncover a secret.
episodes.title: Chapter 70

episodes.synopsis: Claire makes staff changes. The Shepherds try to recruit Doug to their side. With Mark facing intense scrutiny, Jane offers advice.
episodes.title: Chapter 71

episodes.synopsis: While the Shepherd family attempts to diminish Claire's power, Doug goes off the grid but continues angling to advance his agenda.
episodes.title: Chapter 72

episodes.synopsis: Claire tries to tarnish Frank's legacy. Doug provokes Claire by releasing excerpts from Frank's diary. A rift develops between the Shepherds.
episodes.title: Chapter 73
